Description: Bronze incense-burner; one terminal in the form of a papyrus-head issuing a hand holding a vessel(now missing); cartouche-shaped receptacle supported by the figure of a kneeling king halfway along the main shaft; separate bronze hawk-head terminal fits onto a wooden tang bound with papyrus.
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: Prof Walter B Emery
Curator's comments: Published: W. Seipel, Ägypten Vol. 1, Linz 1989, p.186 [151. S. Davies and H.S. Smith, The sacred animal necropolis at North Saqqara, MEES 73, 2005, p. 114
Bibliographic references: Insley Green 1987 / The temple furniture from the sacred animal necropolis at North Saqqara, 1964-1976 (86)
